We couldn't have asked for a better start.
The photographs on display here were taken by Arni Saeberg, a photographer for Morgunblaðið, during the filming of an advertisement with the title "Let It Out" in the middle of last month.
Filming took place all over Iceland, such as on Skólavörðustíg in Reykjavík, at Reynisfjara, at Skógarfoss, at Sólheimajökull and in a cave at Hjörleifshöfði.
The directors were Samúel Bjarki Pétursson and Gunnar Páll Ólafsson from Skoti productions and the cinematographer was Óttar Guðnason.
The Icelandic Anna Jia and Murphy Cardenas, who is from Cuba and Hungary, starred in the film.
Dozens of Icelanders were involved in the making of the ads, while filming was taking place in the south of the country, another group was working in the west and westfjords.
According to Egill, "Let It Out" is only the first part of the Looks Like You Need Iceland campaign, with a winter campaign planned in collaboration with M&C Saatchi.
This is just the first phase of the work for the Icelandic Tourist Board, says Egill and adds that the collaboration with M&C Saatchi has gone very well.
